      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "That's a good hint to add to the `README`. But having the root key not too recent still seems better, all things equal. I think we should only bump it if a former maintainer revokes their key or it expires, plus maybe every couple of years to preempt such issues. So far #27058 seems compatible with that approach (_update_: not anymore, moving discussion there)",
